caption.text:
Having patience in love is beautiful. It is just like waiting for the Sakura to blossom. I have been waiting from summer, dealing with the heat and letting the sunlight burning my skin. The heat changes my emotion, making me easily to blow up my anger. 
Then, summer turns into winter, where I have to deal with the wind, the snow, and the long night that somehow make me feel so lonely. The coldness kills me inside, making me easily to cry because of my loneliness. 
But, eventually the universe brings back the beauty of spring. The time when I can fully smile. Every step I make becomes magic. singing along with the birds and dancing together with the wind. The Sakura brings me happiness and joy, making me graceful of my life. It always needs time to see the Sakura. But, it makes me love Sakura more. The feeling of waiting makes me never give up loving the Sakura in any circumstances. Because everything is worth the wait. 
And if you can wait to see the Sakura from summer to spring, you can also wait to see the person you love. And you will understand patience for love is beautiful. And waiting for sakura is like waiting for @gilbertmc

caption.text:
A letter from far away island for mama and papa. 
I am not ready to go back. 
I might be dumb that I could not appreciate toward every love I get in each day. I always said "I donnt know who I am, I come from nowhere and I do not belong to anyone." It was not that easy for me to leave my country. Even it was almost impossible. 
Then, I left my country when I just turned 18. Thats the time when young people are looking for "Who Actually They Are". I brought my both sad and beautiful memories. Sad, that I was discriminated by some people in society because I belong to the minority group. Perhaps, because of these experiences, I started not to feel comfortable with the culture. Especially The culture of being hypocrite. For example, drinking and sex, people will screw you up if you drink and have sex with your boyfriend/girlfriend. Its better to reflect on yourself rather than putting comments on others.
And here, the culture is different to what my previous society has taught me. Now, I am living with people from different countries. It means I must adopt and learn the cultures from the beginning. 
Sometimes I am proud of myself because with this young age I can manage and solve everything by myself without involving my parents. It is good. But, on the other hand somehow it makes me lose sense of belonging to my family. It makes me think "I am strong, I can earn money, and with a tent and sleeping bag, I can go and sleep wherever I want." To be honest, I am not ready yet to go back to my home country. Because I still wanna learn more about myself. And the farer I go from my home, The more I know about Who I Am, and the more I appreciate my own country. The way I think, behave, etc might be changed. Perhaps, I am not the person I used to be. But, I am becoming a better person. 
And the thing is I am going back to Indonesia this Saturday just because I want to make my parents happy. Happy anniversary mama and papa. No matter what feelings I am battling with now, you will always be my parents and you have raised me for 18 years.

My story after living in Japan for 6 months. 
It is a joke if I do not say "living far away from family and affording living cost by myself" is easy. In the morning, after I woke up from my sleep, I always got worried whether my money would be enough to cover my daily needs for each day. Consequently, I became workaholic to do part time jobs. I knew some others international students felt the same thing because we did not ask money from our parents. But, as time went by I became crazier and exhausted. Not only thinking about the money, but we had to focus on classes also, studying hard to get good GPA. Sometimes, I cried in the silence and asked "Why does it feel so tough sometimes? And why can not I completely enjoy my life of being a teen?" I started to think there must be something wrong with me. Something wrong that makes me can not enjoy every single moment. Since I was kid, I have been dreaming to travel the world. So, I threw all my fears and decided to travel by my own salary. Yes, I saved a lot but I used to get worried about the future. what if I would not have enough money for next month? What if I would have to pay health insurance? What if.. What if... And too much what if and questions about things that I did not face yet. After meeting with many travelers from different countries and reading books about traveling, my mind changed "What is the point if I save a lot of money but I am gonna die one day? Even I do not have any clue when I will die. So, I will live my dream and start to be happy!" Now I am a happy human being! I enjoy every single day! I manage everything! I never forget my duty to study, but I also have part time job. I travel a lot, but I also volunteer and do other valuable activities. I can be like this because I am not alone, Jesus is always with me. Now I understand, the key of being happy is simple. Be grateful and follow your dream :)
